The paper discusses a new approach for solving functional constraints in Constraint Programming (CP) systems, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Programming Languages (PL). The paper also mentions the use of local consistency algorithms, which are commonly used in Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs) and can be categorized under Logic and Computation (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the reduction of systems involving functional and bi-functional constraints, which can be categorized under Data Structures (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
